  "prompt": "What's your definition of \"friends\"?",
  "response": "Friendship is a close and mutual relationship between individuals characterized by trust, support, affection, and understanding. Friends share common interests, values, or experiences and often engage in activities together that strengthen their bond. Key aspects of friendship include:\n\n1. **Trust and Reliability:** Friends can depend on each other, knowing that confidences are kept and promises are honored.\n2. **Emotional Support:** Friends provide comfort and encouragement during both good times and challenging moments.\n3. **Mutual Respect:** Friends respect each other\u2019s opinions, boundaries, and individuality.\n4. **Communication:** Open and honest communication allows friends to express their thoughts and feelings freely.\n5. **Shared Experiences:** Engaging in activities, hobbies, or interests together helps build a deeper connection.\n6. **Empathy and Understanding:** Friends strive to understand each other\u2019s perspectives and show compassion.\n7. **Loyalty:** Friends stand by each other, offering steadfast support and standing up for one another when needed.\n\nFriendships can vary in depth and duration, ranging from casual acquaintances to lifelong companions. They play a crucial role in personal well-being, providing a sense of belonging, enhancing emotional health, and contributing to overall happiness. Good friendships are built on a foundation of mutual care, respect, and a willingness to invest time and effort into maintaining the relationship.",
